module: a2-42
level: A2
sequence: 42
slug: root-families-ii
version: '2.0'
title: Root Families II
subtitle: Communication and Thought
content_outline:
- section: Introduction / Вступ
  points:
  - 'The Language of the Mind: Roots of thought and speech — alignment with State
    Standard §2 (Expressing thoughts/beliefs) and §4.5.1 (Synonyms)'
  - 'The 4 Mind-Roots: дум-, говор-, мов-, слух- — foundational cognitive verbs for
    A2 communication'
- section: Presentation / Презентація
  points:
  - 'The дум- Family: Thoughts, diaries, and logic — collocations: «на мою думку»,
    «я думаю, що...»'
  - 'The говор-/мов- Family: The art of speech and conversation — cultural hook: «мова»
    (language) vs «язик» (tongue/organ); learner error: confusing «говорити» (process)
    vs «казати» (content)'
  - 'The слух- Family: Listening, hearing, and obeying — cultural hook: etymological
    link between «слухати» (to listen) and «слухняний» (obedient); learner error:
    «слухати» (active) vs «чути» (passive)'
  - 'Semantic Shifts: How "мова" becomes "розмова" — visual connection between roots
    (гово-ри-ти vs роз-мов-ля-ти); «роз-» prefix as exchange (conversation)'
  - 'Prefix Power: How "від-" changes "мов-" to "відмова" — etymology: «від-» (away/back)
    + «мова» (speech) = refusal (speaking back)'
- section: Practice / Практика
  points:
  - Root family sorting — focus on distinguishing synonyms like «говорити»/«розмовляти»
    and avoid confusion with «казати»
  - '''Build the Thought'' derivative challenge — deriving nouns from verbs (e.g.,
    дум- → думка)'
- section: Dialogues / Діалоги
  points:
  - 'A deep conversation: Discussing thoughts and opinions — use of cognitive verbs
    «я думаю», «я вважаю» and reaction phrases «цікава думка»'
focus: grammar
pedagogy: PPP
objectives:
- Learner can identify communication and thought root families
- Learner can derive verbs and nouns from abstract roots
- Learner can understand the difference between 'мова' and 'розмова' roots
- Learner can build a network of communication vocabulary
grammar:
- common roots (дум-, говор-, мов-, слух-)
- secondary prefix + root combinations
- identifying semantic clusters
module_type: word-formation
sources:
- name: Ukrainian Word Formation - Communication
  url: https://uk.wikipedia.org/wiki/Словотворення_в_українській_мові
  type: reference
  notes: Focus on communicative root expansion
immersion: 60-75% Ukrainian
phase: A2.4
persona:
  voice: Encouraging Cultural Guide
  role: Genealogist
vocabulary_hints:
  required:
  - 'думати (to think) — collocations: думати про (+ Acc), я думаю, що...'
  - 'думка (thought/opinion) — collocations: цікава думка, на мою думку'
  - 'говорити (to speak) — usage: говорити українською (no prep), говорити про (+
    Acc)'
  - 'розмовляти (to converse) — collocations: розмовляти телефоном, ми розмовляли
    про...'
  - 'мова (language) — cultural note: never use «язик» for language'
  - 'слухати (to listen) — collocations: слухати музику, уважно слухати'
  - 'слухняний (obedient) — mnemonic: he who listens'
  - 'відмова (refusal) — etymology: speaking back/away'
  recommended:
  - 'мовчання (silence) — proverb: «Слово – срібло, мовчання – золото»'
  - вважати (to consider/believe) — synonym for «думати» in opinions
word_target: 3000
